  "prompt": "What are some good romantic movies with unusual ideas?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are some romantic movies with unusual or unique concepts that have captivated audiences:\n\n1. **Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind** (2004) - This film explores the complexities of relationships and memories through a unique narrative where characters use a procedure to erase memories of their past lovers.\n\n2. **Her** (2013) - A lonely writer develops an unlikely relationship with an operating system designed to meet his every need. This movie delves into the connection between humans and technology.\n\n3. **The Shape of Water** (2017) - Set against the backdrop of the Cold War, this fairy tale-like love story evolves between a mute woman and an amphibious creature contained in a government facility.\n\n4. **Scott Pilgrim vs. The World** (2010) - A blend of romance and action, Scott Pilgrim must defeat his new girlfriend's seven evil exes in epic video game-style battles to win her heart.\n\n5. **Ruby Sparks** (2012) - A struggling novelist creates a character named Ruby who inexplicably comes to life, leading to both comedic and heartwarming moments as he navigates the consequences.\n\n6. **WALL-E** (2008) - This animated feature showcases a love story between two robots amidst a post-apocalyptic Earth, highlighting themes of loneliness and hope.\n\n7. **Seeking a Friend for the End of the World** (2012) - With an impending asteroid set to destroy the planet, two strangers set off on an unexpected journey together in this endearing apocalyptic romantic comedy.\n\n8. **About Time** (2013) - A man discovers he can travel through time and uses this ability to improve his love life and his relationships, bringing a heartfelt perspective on life's moments.\n\n9. **The One I Love** (2014) - A couple's weekend getaway takes a bizarre twist as they confront surreal events that challenge their perception of each other and their relationship.\n\n10. **Timer** (2009) - In a world where people can see a countdown to when they meet their soulmate, the film follows a woman whose timer hasn't started, leading her to question fate and love.\n\nThese films offer imaginative takes on romance and relationships, making them stand out with their unique plotlines and inventive storytelling.",
